This rule applies to commit messages

# Rule content

IMPORTANT: always start commit with the Ticket/Issue number (`#XXXXX`) as follows:

`[#XXXXX] Commit message`

Extract the ticket number `#XXXXX` from the current branch name, eg:

`XXXXX_branch_name` -> `[#XXXXX] Commit message`

Keep commit messages concise and structured.

Keep the meaning strongly to the point of the changes.

Keep the length to the minimum.

As a context read the @.cursor\rules\cmwhelp.mdc rule

